<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="487" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,332,645]" box="[199,1179,367,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,1017,367,392]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Recorded damage and economic importance in the orchards of Iran:</emphasis>
Not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,332,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,946,404,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
A phytoplasma vector which is commonly found in vineyards and may play a role in transferring Grapevine Yellows (GY), Bois noir/ Stolbur and Aster yellows (AY) (
<bibRefCitation box="[316,514,476,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref17908" refString="Batlle, A., Martinez, M. A. &amp; Lavina, A. (2000) Occurrence, distribution and epidemiology of Grapevine Yellows in Spain. European Journal of Plant Pathology, 106, 811 - 816. https: // doi. org / 10.1023 / A: 1008794905178" type="journal article">
Batlle 
<emphasis box="[392,440,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[525,763,476,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref21144" refString="Orenstein, S., Zahavi, T., Nestle, D., Shardon, R., Barkalifa, M. &amp; Weintraub, P. G. (2003) Spatial dispersion patterns of potential leafhopper and planthopper (Homoptera) vectors of phytoplasma in wine vineyards. Annals of Applied Biology, 142 (3), 341 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7348.2003. tb 00259. x" type="journal article">
Orenstein 
<emphasis box="[641,691,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[775,974,476,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref18168" refString="Bosco, D., Alma, A &amp; Arzone, A. (2008) Studies on population dynamics and spatial distribution of leafhoppers in vineyards (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Annals of Applied Biology, 130 (1), 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7348.1997. tb 05778. x" type="journal article">
Bosco 
<emphasis box="[852,901,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[986,1180,476,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref19792" refString="Landi, L., Isidoro, N. &amp; Riolo, P. (2013) Natural Phytoplasma Infection of Four Phloem-Feeding Auchenorrhyncha Across Vineyard Agroecosystems in Central-Eastern Italy. Journal of Economic Entomology, 106 (2), 604 - 613. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / EC 12400" type="journal article">
Landi 
<emphasis box="[1058,1107,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1192,1396,476,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref20366" refString="Minuz, R. L., Isidoro, N., Casavecchia, S., Burgio, G. &amp; Riolo, P. (2013) Sex-dispersal differences of four phloem-feeding vectors and their relationship to wild-plant abundance in vineyard agroecosystems. Journal of Economic Entomology, 106 (6), 2296 - 309. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / EC 13244" type="journal article">
Minuz 
<emphasis box="[1272,1320,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,332,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,571,511,536]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">
Recorded distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[508,565,511,536]" name="Iran" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Iran</collectingCountry>
:
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[581,682,511,536]" country="Israel" name="Southern" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Southern</collectingRegion>
slopes of 
<collectingRegion box="[805,882,511,536]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Alborz</collectingRegion>
to south and southwest (
<bibRefCitation pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref20841" refString="Mozaffarian, F. &amp; Wilson, M. R. (2016) A checklist of the leafhoppers of Iran (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 4062 (1), 1 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4062.1.1" type="journal article">Mozaffarian &amp; Wilson 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,332,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,583,608]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">Conclusion:</emphasis>
The vector status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herrich-Schaeffer" authorityYear="1834" box="[598,758,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Neoaliturus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestratus">
<emphasis box="[598,758,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">N. fenestratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
needs further study in Iran. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1100,1339,583,608]" pageId="12" pageNumber="487" refId="ref18567" refString="Dehghan, S., Salehi, M., Khanchezar, A., Rastegari, N. &amp; Salari, M. (2012) Transmission characteristics of lettuce phyllody phytoplasma by Neoaliturus fenestratus in Fars, Iran. Journal of Plant Pathology, 48 (1), 35 - 36." type="journal article">
Dehghan 
<emphasis box="[1212,1265,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="487">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
showed transmission of Lettuce Phyllody (LP) by this species.
</paragraph>
